  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The shroud screen advertisement hereby permitted shall not be displayed until all the scaffold is in place and shall be removed when the scaffold is removed or within 12 months of the advertisement's initial display, whichever is the sooner. \r\nReason: The advertisement is only acceptable for a limited period, having regard to the amenity of the area in accordance with Council policy DMS8 of the Development Management Policies Document (adopted March 2016) and the requirements of paragraph 136 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021.\r\n",
    "Condition : 2 - The area of the inset advertising shall not exceed 8.4m x 5.5m and shall always form part of the larger shroud screen advertisement hereby permitted for the duration of the display. \r\nReason: To ensure the sign does not have an adverse effect on the amenity of the area in accordance with Council policy DMS8 and to comply with paragraph 136 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021.\r\n",
    "Condition : 3 - No part of the shroud screen advertisement hereby permitted shall be illuminated.\r\nReason: To ensure the sign does not have an adverse effect on the amenity of the area and neighbouring residential amenity in accordance with Council policies DMS8 and DMS1 and to comply with paragraph 136 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021.\r\n"
  ],
